Reasoning: The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms for finding connected $f$-factors in graphs with large minimum degree. This topic falls under several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Graph Theory (cs.GT), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). However, since the paper focuses primarily on graph theory and algorithms, we believe that cs.DM, cs.DS, and cs.GT are the most likely sub-categories. The paper may also be relevant to researchers in computational geometry and distributed computing, but to a lesser extent.
